What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Limestone for Agriculture Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Limestone for Agriculture Market

Limestone for agriculture market is expected to gain market growth in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. Data Bridge Market Research analyses the market to grow at a CAGR of 5.80% in the above-mentioned forecast period.

Limestone for agriculture market deal with the sale and consumption of the agricultural limestone. Limestone for agriculture basically contains natural nutrients to promote healthy plant growth. It is a soil amendment product that is generally utilized to condition soil by raising pH levels. The limestone for agriculture is available in various types such as the normal, and granular/palletized. It is basically added to agricultural crops and then it further dissolves and releases a base that counteracts or neutralizes soil acidity. The limestone for agriculture is basically of different types such as calcitic, dolomitic and other which are used for various applications such as the agriculture and the gardening.

The growing usages of normal limestone in accelerating the speed and increase the effectiveness emerge as the major significant factor fostering the growth of the limestone for agriculture market. In addition to this, the factors such as increasing benefits such as maintaining a balance between physical, chemical and biological properties of the soil coupled with the rising applications in agriculture, construction, steel, glass, and others are further estimated to cushion the growth of the market in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. Moreover, its advantageous particle size and controlled and effortless applications, it also finds application in the production of steel and iron, water and wastewater treatment, construction, agriculture, paper and pulp, and chemical industry, among others are also projected to accelerate the market’s growth within the above mentioned forecast period. On the other hand, the factors such as the increasing health hazards associated with calcium carbonate impedes the growth of the limestone for agriculture market in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. Additionally, the dearth of veterinary practitioners for livestock is also expected to hamper the overall growth of the market.

Furthermore, the growing number of development and expansion activities which will increase the availability of superior quality limestone products will create lucrative opportunities for the growth of the limestone for agriculture market. On the flip side, the factors such as the temporary disruption caused due to restrictions and lockdown due to COVID-19 has effected the market negatively and thus is projected to challenge the market within the forecast period.

